Rating: 4
Instead of the lemon juice I used raspberry vinegar and I left out the chives. I added some salt and black pepper and I stirred the almonds through the salad. It was absolutely delicious next to my Greek meatballs in tomato sauce.

Rating: 3
Thanks to other reviewers, I tweaked this. With the tweaks, it was quite good. Here's what I did: reduce lemon juice to 2 teaspoons, substitute 3 T. mayonnaise for the olive oil, add a touch of garlic, and don't be shy with the salt! I used Fage 2% greek yogurt. Big Yum! Served with indian spiced lamb chops and naan from Trader Joes.

